  "text": "To conclude this section, we provide some insight into the feasibility of the QP problems (18) and (22) . It has already been reported in [CITATION_1] that the nominal MPC for walking with fixed footstep positions and without external forces is always feasible. It can be easily demonstrated that this property remains for the MPC formulations presented here. Perpetual feasibility, however, does not guarantee that the generated CoM motion does not diverge, leading to robot fall.",
